2\. Outage Fix --- E1 Haiku Score Trends

2.1 Root Cause

The Haiku Score Trends node in ELECTRON-1 was calling Claude Haiku 4.5
with max_tokens: 8192. The prompt asked for 10-15 trends plus
avoided_topics, each with full source URLs. The total output regularly
exceeded 8192 tokens, resulting in truncated JSON. The downstream parser
had no truncation repair, so it returned {success: false, error: \'No
trends found\'}. The PostgreSQL INSERT node tried to store this error
object, which failed because \'success\' is not a column in trend_board.

2.2 Fix Applied --- Haiku Score Trends v2.2

  ---------------------- ------------------------ ------------------------
  **Change**             **Before**               **After**

  Trend count            10-15                    7-10

  Descriptions           Unlimited length         Max 80 characters

  Source URLs per trend  Unlimited                Max 2

  avoided_topics format  Full object with sources id + title + reason only
                                                  (\<100 chars)

  JSON parser            3-layer (no truncation   4-layer (with truncated
                         repair)                  JSON repair)

  Prompt version         2.1                      2.2
  ---------------------- ------------------------ ------------------------

The 4-layer parser: (1) strip markdown fences, (2) direct JSON.parse,
(3) extract outermost {} object, (4) truncation repair --- counts open
brackets, closes them, strips trailing incomplete values.

